tldr: The user requested a comprehensive review and implementation of missing
  features for a sleep questionnaire application. The agent successfully added a
  tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, insufficient sleep syndrome
  detection, outbound links, weighted EDS scoring, full CSV export, and chronic
  fatigue/pain screening.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification. The agent identified several
  critical gaps, including a missing tiredness severity scale with safety
  messaging, lack of detection for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome,
  absence of outbound resource links, unweighted EDS scoring, incomplete CSV
  data export, and missing pain/chronic fatigue screening questions. The agent
  then systematically implemented each of these features. This involved updating
  data types, validation schemas, user interface components, and both the
  on-screen and PDF report generation logic. Key additions included a 1-10
  severity slider for tiredness, specific diagnostic logic and recommendations
  for COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, a dedicated resources section with
  external links, a weighted scoring system for EDS, and new questions to screen
  for pain and chronic fatigue symptoms, complete with relevant warnings and
  recommendations. The CSV export was also enhanced to include all collected
  questionnaire data. The implementation was carried out with continuous linting
  to ensure code quality.
